reactions of healthy people to killing circumstances  will speak at Virginia Military Institute on Monday  Oct  20  Grossman s talk   The Bulletproof Mind  Mental Preparation for Combat  will begin at 11 a m  in Gillis Theater in Marshall Hall  Grossman  a former Army Ranger who has taught psychology at the U S  Military Academy  coined the term  killology  in his 2009 Pulitzer nominated book  On Killing  The Psychological Cost of Learning to Kill in War and Society  In the book  he argues that today s media has picked up on the techniques used by armies to teach soldiers to kill  in spite of humans  inborn aversion to killing  and that the media is thus responsible for the rising rate of school shootings and other violent acts among the young  On Killing is on the U S  Marine Corps Commandant s required reading list and is also required reading at the Federal Bureau of Investigations academy  One of the world s foremost experts on killing and human violence in general  Grossman helped to train mental health professionals after the Jonesboro  Ark  school shooting  and has also been involved with either counseling or court cases in the wake of the Paducah  Springfield  Littleton  Virginia Tech  and Nickel Mines Amish school shootings  In addition  Grossman served as a member of the prosecutor s team in the case against convicted Oklahoma City bomber Timothy McVeigh  Today  he spends over three quarters of the year on the road training law enforcement and military personnel  Grossman is a member of the American Board for Certification in Homeland Security and the American College of Forensic Examiners Institute  Grossman s talk is part of the H B  Johnson Jr   26 Distinguished Lecture Series   VMI Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Institute Report Photos   Videos Cindy Bither Administrative Assistant P   540  464 7207 F   540  464 7443 111 Smith Hall Lexington  VA 24450  Communications   Marketing News and Features Construction News Instit